! Cytoscape Engine

An alternative graph rendering engine for [[tw-graph|$:/plugins/flibbles/graph]] powered by [[Cytoscape.js|https://js.cytoscape.org/]] (v3.33.2).

!! Key Features

* ''Drop-in replacement'' for vis-network — existing `<$graph>` markup works unchanged
* ''Compound/container nodes'' — group nodes visually by setting a `cluster` attribute on `<$node>`
* ''COSE layout'' — Compound Spring Embedder layout that handles nested node groups natively
* Full event support: hover, click, drag, double-click
* Position persistence and physics simulation
* Declarative stylesheet with per-element style overrides

!! Quick Start

# Install this plugin alongside `flibbles/graph`
# Go to ''Settings > Graph Engine'' and select ''Cytoscape''
# All existing graphs render with Cytoscape.js

!! Compound Nodes

The key differentiator over vis-network. Add a `cluster` attribute to any `<$node>` — its value must be the `$tiddler` of another node in the same graph:

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="Team" label="Team Alpha"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Person1" label="Alice" cluster="Team"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Person2" label="Bob" cluster="Team"/>
</$graph>
```

Alice and Bob render inside a container labeled "Team Alpha". The `cluster` attribute is separate from the domain model's `parent` field — it controls visual grouping only and is ignored by vis-network.

!! Prerequisites

* `$:/plugins/flibbles/graph` (tw-graph) v1.6.0+
* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+
